<TITLE> 'Top outlaw' killed in Pabna encounter </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  A suspected leader of outlawed extremist outfit Purba Bangla Communist Party was killed in a shootout with law enforcers at Santhia in Pabna early Friday, police said. Pabna police super Nibash Chandra Majhi said 32 year-old Saad Ali aka Akash was a "military leader" of PBCL (ML-Janajuddha). Majhi told bdnews24.com police received a tip-off that a group of PBCL operatives were holding a clandestine meeting in Madarbaria village. He said a police squad went to the spot at around 1:15am. "The criminals opened fire at police forcing them to shoot back," said the police super. At one stage of shootout the criminals fled the scene. Police found Saad Ali's body left behind. One shutter gun and six rounds of bullets were also recovered, said Majhi. The police super said Saad Ali faced 16 cases including eight for murder. bdnews
